      "text": "# Interconnection Deposit Financing: A Novel Approach - Project Finance/PPP & PFI - United States\n\nPublished: 2026-02-24T19:26:24+00:00\nAuthor: Edward J. Hammond\n\n## Summary\n\nFoley & Lardner LLP has taken a novel approach to financing interconnection deposits for renewable energy projects, particularly in the US, Mexico, Europe and Asia. The loan was sized using a \"borrowing base\" consisting of refundable interconnections, which were pledged as collateral to the lender. As projects progressed through development, these deposits became non-refundable and the lender had the right to withdraw the project from the interconnection queue if necessary. This model allows for lower borrowing costs and more efficient use of assets in project development. The firm believes this model could be applied to future projects.\n\n## Story\n\nInterconnection Deposit Financing: A Novel Approach - Project Finance/PPP & PFI - United States ARTICLE 24 February 2026 # Interconnection Deposit Financing: A Novel Ap",
